ZH: 我们应该哀悼那些在这场灾难中失去生命的人。
EN: We should mourn those who lost their lives in this disaster.

ZH: 这次国家哀悼日是为了纪念逝去的英雄。
EN: This national day of mourning is to commemorate the fallen heroes.

ZH: 他们戴着黑纱哀悼逝去的亲人。
EN: They wore black veils to mourn their deceased loved ones.

ZH: 在哀悼仪式上，人们默哀长达一分钟。
EN: During the mourning ceremony, people observed a minute of silence.

ZH: 我们要向遇难者表示哀悼和慰问。
EN: We express our condolences and sympathy to the victims.

ZH: 全国人民都在哀悼国家的损失。
EN: The entire nation mourns the loss of the country.

ZH: 他们为失去的亲人深感哀悼。
EN: They deeply mourn for their deceased loved ones.

ZH: 时间会让我们感受到哀悼的重量。
EN: Time will make us feel the weight of mourning.

ZH: 哀悼曲在葬礼上奏响，让人们感到悲伤。
EN: The dirge played at the funeral, evoking sadness.

ZH: 每年的今天，我们都会哀悼这个国家曾经的痛苦历史。
EN: On this day every year, we mourn the painful history of this country.

ZH: 他们举行了一场隆重的哀悼仪式来纪念已故总统。
EN: They held a solemn memorial service to commemorate the deceased president.

ZH: 哀悼活动使人们能够共同分享痛苦和悲伤。
EN: Mourning events allow people to share pain and sorrow together.

ZH: 在哀悼的日子里，我们应该停下脚步，默哀表示敬意。
EN: On days of mourning, we should pause and observe a moment of silence to show respect.

ZH: 他们为全国的哀悼做出了自己的贡献。
EN: They made their own contributions to the national mourning.

ZH: 哀悼之日，寂静占据了整个城市。
EN: On the day of mourning, silence filled the entire city.

ZH: 我们应该为那些不幸的事件表达哀悼之情。
EN: We should express our condolences for those unfortunate events.

ZH: 哀悼是一种对逝者的敬意和追忆。
EN: Mourning is a sign of respect and remembrance for the deceased.

ZH: 哀悼需要时间来缓解内心的痛苦。
EN: Mourning takes time to alleviate the pain in our hearts.

ZH: 出于对逝者的哀悼，人们戴上黑色服装。
EN: In mourning for the deceased, people wear black clothing.

ZH: 哀悼的日子，哭泣成为了最好的发泄方式。
EN: On days of mourning, crying becomes the best way to release emotions.
